  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You're under arrest.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And with that, he was taken to a jail.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "After spending several days in this awful jail, he was told, if you promise to give up your business, give up your home, and leave town, and never come back again, we will release you.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And since he wanted so desperately to get out, he made that promise.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But now, he no longer had a source of income.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "He no longer had a place to live.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And so he came to live with us.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And at first, I thought it was wonderful having Grandpa there every day, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] until I found out why and began to understand why he was so unhappy.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "He spent several months with us.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And then when he felt that maybe it was too much for us, he moved on to my uncle and aunt's home, to his son and daughter-in-law, and spent several months with them.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "That was my uncle, Manfred, M-A-N-F-R-E-D, and my aunt, Else, E-L-S-E.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And he spent several months with them.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And then when he felt it was maybe too much for them, he moved on to an old age home, spent some time there.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And then came back to us, and then onto my uncle and aunt, and so on.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "The next major thing that really happened would take me to November 9 and November 10, 1938, which is Crystal Night, or the Night of the Broken Glass.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] The night of, of, of November 9, I remember my parents shutting the, the shutters on the windows, and my father saying to me, if you hear any noise during the night, get up out of bed immediately and go and sit in the wardrobe in the hallway.",
      "word_count": 52
    }
  ],
